[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/OpenStack OpenStack] Swift is a highly available, distributed, eventually consistent object/blob store, which MediaWiki can use as a storage backend for media files and their derivatives (thumbnails, transcodes etc), together with associated headers and metadata.

== Debugging ==
The <code>swift</code> command-line client can be used for debugging:
* <code>swift list</code>: list all containers (the Swift equivalent of directories)
* <code>swift list --prefix wiki-dev-local-public</code>: list containers for public files
* <code>swift list <container></code>: list files in a container
* <code>swift stat <container> <file></code>: show data stored for a file

A log of recent operations is in <code>/vagrant/logs/swift/object-server.log</code>.

